    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Architectural style that developed particularly in Italy in the 1920s and 1930s, that emphasized a scientific and rational approach to design, prioritizing functional structures, geometric forms, and a rejection of ornamentation. It is  based on theories that emerged during the Renaissance with Vitruvius, in the Enlightenment, and in Neoclassicism.</Note_Text>
